  "text": "Calculations of Renal Oxygenation. Renal oxygen delivery (DO 2ren ) was calculated as RBF ϫ arterial oxygen content: RBF ϫ (1.31 ϫ Hb ϫ SaO 2 ) ϩ (0.003 ϫ PaO 2 ). Renal oxygen consumption (VO 2ren ) was calculated as RBF ϫ (arterial Ϫ renal venous oxygen content difference). Renal venous oxygen content is: (1.31 ϫ Hb ϫ S rv O 2 ) ϩ (0.003 ϫ rv PO 2 ) [CITATION_1] . An estimation of the renal vascular resistance (RVR) of the renal artery flow region was made: RVR ϭ mean arterial pressure (MAP)/RBF [CITATION_2] .",
